(108, NULL, 'Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing', 'parliamentary-forum-for-health', NULL, '<p><strong>Forum:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Advisors: </strong>(Not according to seniority)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dr. A.F.M. Ruhal Haque MP, 107 Satkhira-3</li>\r\n<li>A.S.M. Feroz MP, 112 Patuakhali-2</li>\r\n<li>Begum Meher Afroze Chumki MP, 198 Gazipur-5</li>\r\n<li>Mahabub Ara Begum Gini MP, 30 Gaibandha-2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Chairman:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dr. Md. Habibe Millat MP, 63 Sirajganj-2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Co-Chairmen:</strong>&nbsp;(Not according to seniority)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Md. Shahiduzzaman Sarker MP, 47 Naogaon-2</li>\r\n<li>Aroma Dutta MP, 311 Women Seat-11</li>\r\n<li>Kazi Nabil Ahmed MP, 87 Jashore-3</li>\r\n<li>Barrister Shameem Haider Patwary MP, 29 Gaibandha-1</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Members: </strong>(Not according to seniority)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Nahim Razzaq MP, 223 Shariatpur-3</li>\r\n<li>Shirin Akhter MP, 265 Feni-1</li>\r\n<li>Pir Fazlur Rahman MP, 227 Sunamganj-4</li>\r\n<li>Umme Kulsum Smriti MP, 31 Gaibandha-3</li>\r\n<li>Samil Uddin Ahmed Shimul MP, 43 Chapai Nawabganj-1</li>\r\n<li>Dr. Md. Abdul Aziz MP, 64 Sirajganj-3</li>\r\n<li>Sayeda Zakia Noor MP, 162 Kishoreganj-1</li>\r\n<li>Shabnam Jahan MP, 303 Women&nbsp;Seat-3</li>\r\n<li>Naheed Ezaher Khan MP, 305 Women Seat-5</li>\r\n<li>Aparajita Haque MP, 320 Women Seat-20&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sayeda Rubina Akter MP, 328 Women Seat-28&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Adiba Anjum Mita MP, 337 Women Seat-37&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'page', NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, 28, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(107, NULL, 'Privacy And Policy', 'privacy-and-policy', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 16.8pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">This website is operated by the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation (SSF). The users of this website are subject to the following privacy policy. The Shastho Shurokkha Foundation takes your privacy and the security of your personal information &ndash;meaning any information relating to an identified or identifiable individual &ndash;&nbsp;seriously. Please take a moment to read this privacy policy and learn about the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation&rsquo;s general privacy and information security principles.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 16.8pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">The Shastho Shurokkha Foundation uses secure systems and implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard your personal information and protect it against unauthorized or unlawful processing, accidental loss, destruction, or damage. While we take reasonable measures to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security of your personal information transmitted on our site. You submit your personal information to us at your risk.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 16.8pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">In addition, our policy is to only permit authorized personnel with a legitimate business purpose to access your personal information submitted to our site.&nbsp; Where your personal information is shared with third parties of the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation, we will take reasonable measures to ensure that your personal information is treated securely and in accordance with this privacy policy. These steps may include requiring those companies to implement no less than equivalent security measures than those offered by the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation under this privacy policy. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 16.8pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">You should be aware that information sent to us using the site may not be secure in transmission. Please be aware of this when sending any communications. We cannot (and do not) guarantee absolute security.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">Notification of any change to this privacy policy will be posted on this website. If you have any questions regarding this policy, please contact the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 16.8pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #515151; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">Nothing in or relating to this privacy policy or this site shall be deemed a waiver of any of the privileges and immunities of the Shastho Shurokkha Foundation.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'page', NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\"}', '1', 'frontend', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, 446, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(109, 1, 'Meeting with Hon\'ble Prime Minister Office on 8 March, 2021', 'Meeting-with-Hon\'ble-Prime-Minister-Office', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">Parliamentary Forum, \'Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing\' shared a letter signed by 153 MPs to the Hon\'ble Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">to support the Prime Minister declaration make Bangladesh tobacco free by 2040 and and <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>demanding ban import, production, sale, marketing and use of E-Cigarette before it&rsquo;s become popular in Bangladesh on 8 March 2021, at Prime Minister office. Shastho Shurokkha working as the secretariet of the Forum.&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', '1', 'frontend', 'Prime Minister Office, Dhaka', 'Parliamentary Forum, \'Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing\'  visited Hon\'be Prime Minister Office.', '0', 'post', NULL, 67, 1, NULL, NULL, '1625898881-60415526.jpg', '2021-07-10 06:36:20', '2021-03-08 12:30:00'),
(110, 1, 'Meeting with SDG Coordinator Demanding Tobacco Law Amendment', 'Meeting-with-SDG-Coordinator-Demanding-Tobacco-Law-Amendment', NULL, '<p style=\"margin: 0in; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 115%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; color: black;\">Founder chairman of Shastho Shurokkha Foundation and chairman of&nbsp;&nbsp;&lsquo;Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing&rsquo; along with&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Dr. Nizam Uddin Ahmed, executive director, and Mr. Md. Rafiqul Islam, director met with&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Juena Aziz, Chief Coordinator (SDG) and&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Mr. Mohd. Monirul Islam, joint secretary (SDGs) of Prime Minister Office&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; color: black;\">to emphasizes the importance of amending tobacco control law to achieve Sustainable Development Goals (SDG) and build a tobacco-free Bangladesh on</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; color: black;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;23</span><sup style=\"text-align: justify;\">rd</sup><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;March 2021.</span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 115%; margin: 12.0pt 0in .0001pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: major-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: major-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: major-latin; color: black;\">On behalf of the BPFHW, the chairman Prof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat MP informed Juena Aziz about the harmful aspects of tobacco. Referring to the declaration of Tobacco Free Bangladesh by 2040 announced by the Hon\'ble Prime Minister, he informed about the various initiatives taken by the MPs in this regard including the recommendation to amend the existing Tobacco Control Law. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '1', 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Prime Minister Office, Dhaka', 'Founder chairman of Shastho Shurokkha Foundation and chairman of  ‘Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing’ along with Dr. Nizam Uddin Ahmed, executive director, and Mr. Md. Rafiqul Islam, director met with Juena Aziz, Chief Coordinator (SDG) and Mr. Mohd. Monirul Islam, joint secretary (SDGs) of Prime Minister Office to emphasizes the importance of amending tobacco control law to achieve Sustainable Development Goals (SDG) and build a tobacco-free Bangladesh on 23rd March 2021.', '0', 'post', NULL, 40, 19, NULL, NULL, '1625901106-39977262.jpg', '2021-07-10 07:56:57', '2021-03-23 14:56:00'),
(111, NULL, '“Tobacco Taxation in 2021-22 National Budget: Things to do”', 'Tobacco-Taxation-in-2021-22-National-Budget-Things-to-do', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A virtual seminar organized by \'Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing\' supported by Shastho Shurokkha Foundation on 4th May, 2021. The seminar&nbsp;<span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; color: black; background: white; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">was presided over by BPFHW forum chairman Prof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat, MP; where the Deputy Speaker of Jatiya Sangsad; Mr. Fazle Rabbi Miah, MP present as a chief guest and Prof. Dr. AFM Ruhal Haque present as special guest. Keynote presentation given by chairman of Unnayan Shamonnay and&nbsp;former governor of Bangladesh Bank, Dr. Atirur Rahman. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; color: black; background: white; mso-bidi-language: BN;\">Through the keynote presentation, two proposals were put forward for the implementation of a specific tax on tobacco in the upcoming budget. Those are, increasing the price of cigarettes at all tires, especially low-tire cigarettes, increasing retail price. Another one is, reduce tobacco use and increase revenue by formulating and implementing effective tobacco tax policy for a period of 5 years.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">Including 18 anti-tobacoc organization, a total of 16 Members of Parliament perticipated at the seminar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-ideograph; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Virtual', 'A virtual seminar organized by \'Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing\' supported by Shastho Shurokkha Foundation on 4th May, 2021.', '0', 'post', NULL, 47, 19, NULL, NULL, '1625902206-12380939.png', '2021-07-10 07:56:19', '2021-05-04 10:56:00'),
(112, 1, 'Meeting with NBR Chairman', 'Meeting-with-NBR-Chairman', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-02fab4ec-7fff-5fa1-ba57-7eec3a71150d\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Verdana; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">On 12 April 2021, a meeting was held with Mr. Abu Hena Md. Rahmatul Munim, Chairman of National Board of Revenue (NBR) by the participation of members of &lsquo;Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing&rsquo;. In this meeting on behalf of Forum several proposals were put forward regarding the tobacco tax hike. Chairman of the forum Prof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat MP handed over a copy of a letter signed by 52 MPs to the NBR chairman on demanding tobacco taxation.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'National Board of Revenue Office (NBR), Dhaka', 'On 12 April 2021, a meeting was held with Mr. Abu Hena Md. Rahmatul Munim, Chairman of National Board of Revenue (NBR) by the participation of members of ‘Bangladesh Parliamentary Forum for Health and Wellbeing’.', '0', 'post', NULL, 48, 19, NULL, NULL, '1625902801-96265577.jpg', '2021-07-10 07:55:44', '2021-04-12 13:55:00'),
(113, NULL, 'Meeting with Health Secretary', 'Meeting-with-health-secretary', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Executive Director of SS Foundation Dr. Nizam Uddin Ahmed and Director Md. Rafiqul Islam met with Health Secretary Mr. Lokman Hossain Mia on 27th june, 2021 to share a letter signed by 152 MPs demanding tobacco law amendment as part of follow up meeting with Hon\'ble Health Minister.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Dhaka', 'Executive Director of SS Foundation Dr. Nizam Uddin Ahmed and Director Md. Rafiqul Islam met with Health Secretary Mr. Lokman Hossain Mia on 27th june, 2021 to share a letter signed by 152 MPs demanding tobacco law amendment as part of follow up meeting.', '0', 'post', NULL, 38, 19, NULL, NULL, '1625903070-54952327.jpg', '2021-07-10 07:51:14', '2021-06-27 13:50:00'),
(114, 1, 'Formation of school club, \'Shastho Shurokkha Club\'', 'Formation-of-school-club', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On 26th June, 2021 SS Foundation visited Mallika Sanaullah Ansari Junior School and Jamtoil Govt. High School at Sirajganj District to form school club, \'Shastho Shurokkha Club\' and distributed COVID-19 safety kits among the students to prevent pandemic, tree plantation and promoted understanding of tobacco control issues.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Sirajganj', 'SS Foundation visited Mallika Sanaullah Ansari Junior School and Jamtoil Govt. High School at Sirajganj District to form school club, \'Shastho Shurokkha Club\'.', '0', 'post', NULL, 145, 19, NULL, NULL, '1625903613-50244714.jpg', '2021-07-10 07:54:59', '2021-06-26 10:54:00'),
(115, 1, 'COVID-19 Response Food Relief Program', 'COVID-19-Response-Food-Relief-Program', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-5b40fb97-7fff-574a-abbb-9b4db58149ef\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In order to stand by the side of low-income and distressed people during the COVID-19 pandemic, Shastho Shurokkha Foundation has started COVID-19 response emergency food relief program \'Manusher Pashe&nbsp; Amra\' from 11th July in Dhaka and Sirajganj. Everyday almost 700 people are getting mid day meals through this initiative. Mainly low-income, distressed, street children and physically challenged people are benefited by this program. </span></span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Dhaka and Sirajganj', 'In order to stand by the side of low-income and distressed people during the COVID-19 pandemic, Shastho Shurokkha Foundation has started COVID-19 response emergency food relief program \'Manusher Pashe  Amra\' from 11th July in Dhaka and Sirajganj.', '0', 'post', NULL, 46, 19, NULL, NULL, '1627563081-87271055.jpeg', '2021-07-29 12:52:00', '2021-07-11 12:40:00'),
(118, 1, 'Free Oxygen Concentrator just a phone call away', 'Free-Oxygen-Concentrator-just-a-phone-call-away', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-7102daf4-7fff-0212-331e-5bd10ece6959\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The outbreak of COVID-19 is creating new records everyday. Patients are suffering in hospitals, the pressure mounts every time. There is a crisis of oxygen including ICU beds. Various initiatives are being taken by the government to ensure medical services to the patients in the hospitals. According to this, Shastho Shurokkha Foundation has taken an initiative to free oxygen concentrators to support COVID-19 patients in Sirajganj. On 26th July Founder Chairman of the SSF Pof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat, MP inaugurated this program. Through this, patients will get the benefit of free oxygen through just one phone call. It can be used as long as needed.</span></span></p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Sirajganj', 'Shastho Shurokkha Foundation has taken an initiative to free oxygen concentrators to support COVID-19 patients in Sirajganj. On 26th July Founder Chairman of the SSF Pof. Dr. Md. Habibe Millat, MP inaugurated this program. Through this, patients will get the benefit of free oxygen through just one phone call. It can be used as long as needed.', '0', 'post', NULL, 92, 19, NULL, NULL, '1627566749-80923430.jpg', NULL, '2021-07-29 13:52:29'),
(120, 2, 'Bangladesh: Free Oxygen concentrator just a call away', 'https://techobserver.in/2021/08/04/bangladesh-free-oxygen-concentrator-just-a-call-away/?fbclid=IwAR', NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: \'Droid Serif\'; font-size: 17px; color: #222222;\">Free oxygen service is given to COVID-19 patients in Sirajganj by just a&nbsp;<a class=\"st_tag internal_tag\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #003f74; text-decoration-line: none; pointer-events: auto;\" title=\"Phone\" href=\"https://techobserver.in/topic/phone/\" rel=\"tag\">phone</a>&nbsp;call amid the Covid-19 death surge in Bangladesh.&nbsp;Not only that, patients will be given this facility as long as doctor&rsquo;s advised.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: \'Droid Serif\'; font-size: 17px; color: #222222;\">The People of Sirajganj are getting this facility through the support and initiative of the national development organization, &lsquo;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Shastho Shurokkha Foundation&rsquo;</span>.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Sirajganj', 'Free oxygen service is given to COVID-19 patients in Sirajganj by just a phone call amid the Covid-19 death surge in Bangladesh. Not only that, patients will be given this facility as long as doctor’s advised. The People of Sirajganj are getting this facility through the support and initiative of the national development organization, ‘Shastho Shurokkha Foundation’.', '0', 'post', NULL, 0, 19, NULL, NULL, '1628168173-53444973.jpg', NULL, '2021-08-05 12:56:13'),
(121, 1, 'National Mourning Day Observed at Azimpur Orphanage', 'National-Mourning-Day-Observed-at-Azimpur-Orphanage', NULL, '<p>Shastho Shurokkha Foundation observed national mourning day at Azimpur Sir Salimullah Muslim Orphanage.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 'enable', '{\"1\":\"1\",\"2\":\"0\",\"3\":\"0\",\"4\":\"0\"}', NULL, 'frontend', 'Dhaka', 'Shastho Shurokkha Foundation observed national mourning day at Azimpur Sir Salimullah Muslim Orphanage. The foundation organized prayer ceremonies and distributed food among all the children of the orphanage at 19th Aguest, 2021.', '0', 'post', NULL, 16, 19, NULL, NULL, '1629518562-71851863.jpeg', '2021-08-21 05:19:53', '2021-08-19 13:19:00');
