(6, '1651051604-42362235.jpg', 'Mst Sadia Sarkar', 'Assistant Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Mst. Sadia Sarkar was born on 16 December 1989 in Krishnapur village of the 7th Chandai union in Baraigram Upazila of Natore district. Father Md. Sattar Sarkar was a businessman by profession and Mother Mst. Gulnahar Khatun is a housewife. She is the eldest of four brothers and sisters.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">She studied at the primary level in Krishnapur Government Primary School. Later, she was educated at the secondary level in the city union&rsquo;s well-known Panchbaria High School and received a GPA of 2.80 during S. S. C. Subsequently, she pursued H.S.C from Dhanaidaha Khalisadanga Degree College and received a GPA of 2.71. Afterward, she completed B. A. Honors within 4 years and a Master&rsquo;s in Bengali Language and Literature from Rajshahi College, one of the affiliates of the National University with second class.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Other courses:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">She successfully completed the 10th School Teacher Registration Course and 10th Lecturer Teacher Registration Course on Bangla Language and Literature.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">According to Niti Mala (2009) conducted under the Ministry of Social Welfare since 2018, Mst. Sadia Sarkar has successfully served as an Assistant Teacher in Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities and ensure that children with disabilities can become self-reliant by overcoming all the barriers of family and society so that they can get work-oriented education along with reading and writing. All in all, she intends to contribute to shaping the Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy as the best institution in the world through proper groundwork.</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
(7, '1651051842-35085488.jpg', 'Mst Jannatul Ferdousi', 'Assistant Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Mst. Jananatul Ferdousi was born on 6 June 1994 in Chawkbelgharia village of Yusufpur union 1, Charghat Upazila of Rajshahi district. Father Md. Samser Ali was a businessman. Mother Mst. Bilkich Begum was a housewife and a pious woman. She is the second child of her parents among the three sisters.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">She studied at the primary level at Chokbelgharia BRAC School. Educated at the secondary level, she passed the SSC examination with a GPA of 4.75 in the Humanities department from Maskatadighi Multipurpose (Technical) High School, Katakhali Police Station, Rajshahi District, North Bengal. She has completed HSC from Adarsh Degree College and has passed in Humanities Department obtaining a GPA of 4.80. After that, she did B.Sc. Honors for 4 years from the Department of Political Science from Government Rajshahi College and passed with a CGPA of 3.14. She obtained a CGPA of 3.25 in Political Science from Government Rajshahi College and passed the MSS examination. Lastly, she pursued a Bachelor of Special Education (B.S.Ed) from Government Special Education Teacher Training Center.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Other courses:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">She has completed 6 months Computer Office Application Course under Bangladesh Technical Education Board and has obtained an A Plus.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Since 2018, under the Ministry of Social Welfare (2009 Special Education Policy for the Disabled), Mst. Jananatul Ferdousi has been successfully performing her duties as an Assistant Teacher in the Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 19.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities; take initiative and implement it properly so that the children with special needs get vocational education along with academic education so that these children can function as normal people in the society and become independent. Above all, through proper planning, she plans to shape the Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy into the best and most exemplary institution in the world, so that other schools can follow or imitate the institution.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
(9, '1651052001-31975762.jpg', 'Gulshanara Shiba', 'Assistant Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Gulshanara Siba was born on January 1, 1990, in Jotdaibaki village of the first Lalpur union, Lalpur Upazila of Natore district. Father Md. Abul Hashem pursued higher education from Pabna Award College of that time. He later turned his attention to business. Her mother Mrs. Monowara Begum is a housewife. She is the youngest sister of her three brothers.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">She studied at the primary level at Lalpur Khatimunnesa (KN) Government Primary School. Her secondary education was at Lalpur Khatimunnesa (KN) High School, and she graduated from the science department with an &lsquo;A&rsquo; from college. Later, she passed Higher Secondary Examination with &lsquo;B&rsquo; Grade from Science Department, Lalpur Khatimunnesa (KN) High Secondary School and College. Then, she pursued 4 years of BSc Honors and Master&rsquo;s from the Department of Psychology in the second department with success from the renowned National University College, Rajshahi College of Bangladesh.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Other courses:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">She has completed 3-months basic course in computer. Additionally, under the Ministry of Primary and Mass Education, she completed a 15-day long training on child education activities under Reaching Out of School Dildren Rusk Phase-2 project.&nbsp; Also, under the Save the Children and the implementing agency SIP (Social and Economic Enhancement Programme), she pursued a 10-day-long teaching-based training.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">During her graduation, she was employed as a teacher at Shaheen School and College (Rajshahi Branch). Then after completing her Master&rsquo;s, she served as the head teacher for 3 years at the _________________ Government of the People\'s Republic of Bangladesh.&nbsp; Since 2018, under the Ministry of Social Welfare Conducted (as per the 2009 Special Education Policy on Persons with Disabilities) Mst. Gulshanara Siba has been successfully performing her duties as an Assistant Teacher in Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities; take initiative and implement it properly so that the children with special needs get vocational education along with academic education so that these children can function as normal people in society and become independent and pursue a Master&rsquo;s of Special Education (MSED) course in order to improve the quality of education for children with special needs.&nbsp; Above all, through proper planning, she aims to establish Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy as the best and most exemplary institution in the world, so that other schools can follow or imitate the institution.</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
