(13, '1650954226-17305506.jpg', 'Md Rashedul Haque', 'Junior Teacher Gymnastics', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Md. Rashedul Haque was born on 2nd February 1987, in Faridpur village AB 9th AB union, Lalpur Upazila of Natore district. Father Md. Anwarul Haque is an educated man and was an officer of the largest North Bengal Sugar Mill in the Government of the People\'s Republic of Bangladesh and his mother Nahar Haque is a housewife. He is the eldest among two sisters and a brother. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">He was educated at the primary level in Baramhati Government Primary School. Later, he was educated at the secondary level at the reputed school North Bengal Sugar Mills High School (N, B, S, M) where, in the Science department, he received an &lsquo;A&rsquo; grade. Later, at Gopalpur Degree College, he received a \'C\' in the science department at the higher secondary level. Afterward, from the renowned National University College, Rajshahi College, Bangladesh, he successfully passed with the second division of BA Honors and Masters in History. At present, he is studying for a Bachelor of Physical Education (B, P, A, Ed) at Shaheed Ziaur Rahman College, Rajshahi.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Other courses:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">He did a 3-month basic course in computer at the Ministry of Social Welfare, Department of Social service.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">After graduation, in 2014, he has served as a Marketing Officer at a well-known domestic company, Abul Khair Group Company Limited, and the multinational company Reckitt Benckiser with integrity, devotion, and reputation for 2 years and 4 years. Since 2018, under the Ministry of Social Welfare Conducted (as per the 2009 Special Education Policy on Persons with Disabilities) Md. Rashedul Haque has been successfully performing his duties as a Physical Education Teacher in Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans: </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities and take initiative and implement it properly so that the children with special needs get vocational education along with academic education so that these children can function as normal people in society and become independent. He plans to pursue a Bachelor of Physical Education course and implement his knowledge so that he can improve the quality of education the children with special needs are receiving. Above all, through proper planning, he aims to establish Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy as the best and most exemplary institution in the world, so that other schools can follow or imitate the institution.</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
(14, '1651052534-58545619.jpg', 'Md. Firoz Mahmud', 'Junior Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Md. Firoz Mahmud was born on 2nd February 1984 in Faridpur village of Nagar Union 9 of Lalpur police station in Natore district. His father, the late Alhaj Md. Abdul Wahed Miah, was a businessman by profession. Mother Mst. Jamila Begum is a gifted woman. He is the ninth among seven sisters and five brothers.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">He studied at Baramhati Government Primary School and Kujipukur Government Primary School. He studied at Baramhati Cooperative High School and North Bengal Sugar Mills High School, a reputed school in North Bengal, and passed the SSC examination in the first division. He did HSC from Gopalpur Degree College and passed in second class. After that, he did B.Sc. (Hons) from Rajshahi College, Department of Botany. Rolls ranged from 1 to 3 in most classes since childhood.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">After graduation, he worked in a multinational marketing company. Subsequently, since 2016, under the Ministry of Social Welfare (2009 Special Education Policy for the Disabled), Md. Firoz Mahmud has been successfully performing his duties as a Junior Teacher in the Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; color: #52575e; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 14.2667px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities and take steps to improve the quality of education of children with special needs and implement them properly so that these children can move and become like normal people in society. All in all, he intends to shape the Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy as the best institution in the world with the appropriate organization.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
(15, '1651052637-37120530.jpg', 'Mst Nazma Khatun', 'Junior Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Mst. Nazma Khatun was born on 30 December 1990 in Ishwardi village no. 2 of Lalpur Upazila of Natore district. Her father&rsquo;s name is Md. Hazir Uddin Pramanik and mother&rsquo;s name is Mst. Areba Begum. Nazma Khatun is the sixth child of her parents out of seven siblings.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">She completed her primary education at Airport Shohokari Prathomik Biddaloy. Educated at the secondary level, she passed with a GPA of 3.77 from Lalpur Thana Balika (Technical) High School and passed with a GPA of 4.15 at the higher secondary level from Chaknajipur Vocational and Business Management Institute, Natore. After that, she got a GPA of 2.60 from Gopalpur Degree College and passed the degree.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">After successfully passing the degree examination, Nazma Khatun joined Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy in July 2018 as a Junior Assistant Teacher.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #726c7a;\">In order to bring the children with special needs into the mainstream of society and lead a normal life, she joined as a teacher at this school in order to spread the light of education among these children. Her goal is not to make these children a burden to anyone in the future, but to educate these children with special needs and turn them into human resources. As a consequence, these children can play an important role in their own (wealth) and the development of the country.</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
(17, '1650954674-87663011.jpg', 'Taherul Islam', 'Junior Teacher', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Birth:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Taherul Islam was born on 3 October 1995 in Dashgram, 7th Chandai union, Baraigram Upazila of Natore district.&nbsp; Father Md. Amjad Mandal is a farmer and mother Mst. Majeda is a housewife. He is the youngest among three brothers and two sisters.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Education:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">He studied at the primary level in Dashgram Government Primary School. Secondly, he was educated at the secondary level at the famous Dashgram Fazil (Degree) Madrasa of Baraigram Upazila. He passed with a GPA of 5.00 in Dakhil (SSC) examination. He then completed Alim (HSC) from Dashgram Fazil (Degree) Madrasa and passed with a GPA of 4.75. After that, he pursued 4 years long B.Sc Honors from the Chemistry Department from Government Edward College, Pabna, one of the leading institutions in the country.&nbsp; He passed with a CGPA of 3.10. Lastly, he obtained a CGPA of 3.24, 1st class in Chemistry from Government Edward College, Pabna, and passed the M.Sc. examination. Since childhood, his roles ranged from 1 to 5 in most of the classes. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Other courses:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">He has completed 6 months computer office application course from Bangladesh Technical Education Board and achieved an A-plus. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Workplace:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Besides graduation, he has been teaching at Shikhan School for 2 years. He has taught in a kindergarten school after graduation for a year. Besides, he worked as a tutor at Tahera tutorial in the private sector for 2 years. Since 2018, under the Ministry of Social Welfare Conducted (as per the 2009 Special Education Policy on Persons with Disabilities) Taherul Islam has been successfully performing his duties as a Junior Teacher in Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">Future plans</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; color: #726c7a;\">The main goal is to work for the development of children with disabilities and take initiative and implement it properly so that the children with special needs get vocational education along with academic education so that these children can function as normal people in society and become independent. Above all, through proper planning, establish Dhanaidaha Haque Autistic &amp; Buddhi Protibondhi Biddaloy as the best and exemplary institution in the world, so that other schools can follow or imitate the institution.</span></p>', 'https://www.facebook.com/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/', 1),
